        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1260244616" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer178645156421169417">I really like Greg Iles&apos; writing style and the world of Penn Cage&apos;s Mississippi but, <b>holy cow</b>! Does his publisher pay him by the word? One would think that, given 880 pages in which to do it, an author could tell a complete story. But no. Readers who stick it out and get to the end of Natchez Burning will find that quite a few of the bad guys are still alive and free and that many of the good guys are not. Never fear, though. <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/22693231.The_Bone_Tree__Penn_Cage__5_' title='The Bone Tree (Penn Cage #5) by Greg Iles' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Bone Tree</a> is now in the bookstores and after just 816 more pages, </span>
  <span id="freeText178645156421169417" style="display:none">I really like Greg Iles' writing style and the world of Penn Cage's Mississippi but, <b>holy cow</b>! Does his publisher pay him by the word? One would think that, given 880 pages in which to do it, an author could tell a complete story. But no. Readers who stick it out and get to the end of Natchez Burning will find that quite a few of the bad guys are still alive and free and that many of the good guys are not. Never fear, though. <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/22693231.The_Bone_Tree__Penn_Cage__5_" title="The Bone Tree (Penn Cage #5) by Greg Iles" rel="nofollow noopener">The Bone Tree</a> is now in the bookstores and after just 816 more pages, Penn Cage will prevail and the Double Eagles and all of their allies will be dead or in jail. <br /><br />Maybe. <br /><br />Who knows? <br /><br />It could be trilogy.<br /><br />Update: It is.</span>
